oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Johnny Cash - Live in The Annex NCO Club - Tape 1
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Tape 1 of 3. Recording from tape features Carl Perkins (performer) and June Carter (performer) performing on the Johnny Cash Show on an unknown date. Segment was recorded at the Annex 14 NCO Club in Long Binh, Vietnam.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:creator: June Cash; Carl Perkins
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dcterms:tableOfContents: (00:00) Walk the Line (Johnny Cash) -- (00:43) [Unidentified] greets the crowd and introduces Carl Perkins -- (01:41) Freeborn Man (Carl Perkins) -- (04:43) Carl Perkins talks about Jackson, Tennessee and thanks the soldiers for their service -- (05:31) Mean Woman Blues (Carl Perkins) -- (08:12) Carl Perkins introduces "I Can't Help It (If I'm Still In Love With You)" -- (08:30) I Can't Help It (If I'm Still In Love With You) (Carl Perkins) -- (11:09) Jambalaya (On The Bayou) (Carl Perkins) -- (13:13) Perkins introduces "Restless" (13:39) Restless (Carl Perkins) -- (16:29) Carl Perkins expresses his respect for the Tennessee Three, and Perkins talks about Johnny Cash -- (17:09) Blue Suede Shoes (Carl Perkins) -- (18:58) [Unidentified] Expresses their thanks for Perkins and Perkins introduces June Carter Cash -- (20:16) June Carter talks to the audience -- (22:27) June Carter recites a poem -- (24:13) The Last Thing On My Mind (June Carter) -- (26:25) June talks about the Carter Family and introduces the next tune -- (26:53) I Never Will Marry (June Carter) [incomplete]
